Lesquerella fendleri

   [7258.jpg]
   Authority (A. Gray) S. Watson
   Family Magnoliopsida:Dilleniidae:Capparales:Cruciferae
   Synonyms
   Common names bladder-pod, Fendlers bladderpod, yellow-top, desert
   mustard
   Editor
   Ecocrop code 7258

   Notes
   Latitude:
   Altitude: It can be found from sea level up to altitudes of 1200-2100
   m.
   Temperature: Reported temperature range for growth is 8-25°C with the
   optimum between 11-18°C. The crop is cold tolerant.
   Water: Reported annual rainfall range for growth is 300-1100 mm with
   the optimum between 250-1500 mm. It thrives in areas with 250-400 mm
   rainfall from September through April, suggestive of the requirements
   of winter grains. The plant responds well to irrigation.
   Radiation It thrives in full sunlight.
   Range & intensity:
   Photoperiodism:
   Soil:
   Physical: It thrives on calich soil. It is a pioneer on disturbed
   soils, which are dry, open, well-drained sites.
   Chemical: Reported soil pH range for growth is 5.6-8.3 with the optimum
   between 6.5-8. It will not withstand salinity or soils high in gypsum.

   Sources

   FAO - Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - Helping to build a
   world without hunger
